The paper focuses on software process measurement and challenges in Agile Software Development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of the Goal Question Metric (GQM) approach suggests a focus on software process measurement and evaluation, which is also relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). The study involves multiple case studies, which could also be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the challenges faced in operationalizing metrics, which could be relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
